{"word":"ἐξάπτω","slug":"ἐξάπτω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐξάπτω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ψω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to fasten from</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>to</i>, a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>τι ἔκ τινος</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>ἐξ. στόματος λιτάς</el> <i>to let</i> prayers <i>fall from</i> one's mouth, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><el>ἐξ. τί τινι</el> <i>to place upon</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to hang on</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to hang</i> a thing <i>to oneself, carry</i> it <i>about</i> one, <i>wear</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}